    </figure><p>Modern board games can be wonderfully complex and intricate, weaving a web of overlapping mechanics, visual design, and narrative to create a fun and memorable experience every time you play. But before you start <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/51848/183136/4/150237/?merchant=Amazon" rel="sponsored noopener" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/51848/183136/4/150237/?merchant=Amazon">exploring mysterious ruins</a>, <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/25703/136138/4/150238/?merchant=Amazon" rel="sponsored noopener" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/25703/136138/4/150238/?merchant=Amazon">terraforming a planet</a>, or just <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/51844/183131/4/150239/?merchant=Amazon" rel="sponsored noopener" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/51844/183131/4/150239/?merchant=Amazon">building a really nice zoo</a>, you have to learn how to play. And after that, you must take on an even more intimidating task: being the brave soul who tries to <a href="https://www.theonion.com/explanation-of-board-game-rules-peppered-with-reassuran-1819579569" rel="noopener" target="_blank">teach your friends how to play a new board game</a>.</p><div class="f0d316e3"><div class="_664dc41c"><div class="e12e1057 f332f7c7"><div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true" class="_67b9652d"></div><div class="_25a93d02"><span class="_40312379">Dismiss</span></div></div></div></div>]]>
